<eesti>1. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 1 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of application of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatakse turustatava toote ja tootega seotud teenuse ohutuse tagamise n&otilde;uded ning turuj&auml;relevalve korraldamise alused. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) This Act provides safety requirements for marketed products and product-related services and the bases for organisation of market supervision. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esolevat seadust kohaldatakse Eestis turustatavale v&otilde;i Euroopa Liidu liikmesriiki eksporditavale tootele ja tootega seotud teenusele (edaspidi teenus). </eesti>
<inglise>(2) This Act applies to products and product-related services (hereinafter services) marketed in Estonia or exported to a Member State of the European Union. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esolevat seadust kohaldatakse toote ja teenuse ning turuj&auml;relevalve korraldamisele niiv&otilde;rd, kuiv&otilde;rd seda ei ole t&auml;iendavalt reguleeritud teiste seadustega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) This Act applies to products, services and the organisation of market supervision in so far as there are no specific provisions in other Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esolevat seadust ei kohaldata, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) This Act does not apply if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) toodet on kasutatud ja seda on enne uuesti kasutamist vaja parandada v&otilde;i uuendada ning toote turustamisel teavitatakse sellest tarbijat; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a product has been used and must be repaired or reconditioned before re-use and the consumer is notified thereof in the marketing of the product; </inglise>
<eesti>2) isikud pakuvad &uuml;ksteisele toodet v&otilde;i teenust v&auml;ljaspool majandustegevust; </eesti>
<inglise>2) persons supply products or services to one another not in the course of commercial activity; </inglise>
<eesti>3) toodet v&otilde;ib k&auml;sitada kui antiikeset. </eesti>
<inglise>3) a product may be deemed to be an antique. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Toode k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on tarbimiseks valmistatud vallasasi v&otilde;i ehitis kinnisasja olulise osana. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) In this Act, product means a movable manufactured for consumption or a structure as an essential part of an immovable. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Toote turustamine kui majandustegevus k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on toote m&uuml;&uuml;mine v&otilde;i muul viisil tasuta v&otilde;i tasu eest &uuml;leandmine. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) In this Act, marketing of a product in the course of a commercial activity means the sale or transfer by any other means of products, for consideration or not. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Ohutuse m&auml;&auml;ratlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Determination of Safety </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>Ohutu toode ja teenus </eesti>
<inglise>Safe product and safe service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Toode ja teenus on k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses ohutud, kui need, etten&auml;htud v&otilde;i m&otilde;istusp&auml;raselt eeldatavates tingimustes, eesm&auml;rgil ja viisil kasutades, ei ohusta tarbija tervist, turvalisust ja vara. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, products and services are safe if they do not endanger the health, safety or property of a consumer when used under the prescribed conditions or conditions which could be reasonably expected, for the prescribed purposes and in the prescribed manner. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.10.99 j&otilde;ust.14.11.99 - RT I 1999, 82, 753) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.10.99 entered into force 14.11.99 - RT I 1999, 82, 753) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Seaduse v&otilde;i selle alusel muu &otilde;igusaktiga kehtestatud ohutusn&otilde;uete j&auml;rgi kavandatud ja valmistatud toode ning pakutav teenus loetakse ohutuks, kui ta vastab nendele n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Products designed and manufactured or services provided in accordance with the safety requirements established by an Act or other legislation on the basis thereof are deemed to be safe if they comply with such requirements. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Toodet ega teenust ei v&otilde;i pidada ohtlikuks p&otilde;hjusel, et ohutust on v&otilde;imalik suurendada v&otilde;i m&otilde;ni samalaadi toode v&otilde;i teenus on ohutum. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The feasibility of obtaining higher levels of safety or the availability of other similar products presenting a lesser degree of risk shall not constitute grounds for considering a product to be dangerous. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Toodet ei loeta ohutuks, kui selle v&auml;limus, pakend v&otilde;i m&auml;rgistus ei vasta toote sisule v&otilde;i ei v&otilde;imalda &uuml;heselt aru saada selle kasutamise eesm&auml;rgist ning v&otilde;ib seet&otilde;ttu ohustada tarbija tervist, turvalisust ja vara. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A product is not deemed to be safe if its appearance, packaging or labelling does not comply with the composition of the product or does not enable unambiguous comprehension of its purpose and may therefore endanger the health, safety or property of the consumer. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.10.99 j&otilde;ust.14.11.99 - RT I 1999, 82, 753) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.10.99 entered into force 14.11.99 - RT I 1999, 82, 753) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Keelatud on valmistada, turustada, importida ja eksportida toodet, mis ei ole s&ouml;&ouml;dav, kuid mille suurus, kuju, l&otilde;hn, maitse, v&auml;rvus, pakend v&otilde;i m&auml;rgistus on selline, et tarbija, eriti laps, v&otilde;ib seda ekslikult pidada toiduks ja selle suhupanemine, imemine v&otilde;i allaneelamine v&otilde;ib p&otilde;hjustada tervisekahjustusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) It is prohibited to manufacture, market, import or export products which are not edible but the size, shape, odour, flavour, colour, packaging or labelling of which is such that consumers, especially children, may confuse the products with foodstuffs, and the placing in the mouth, sucking or swallowing of which may cause physical harm. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.10.99 j&otilde;ust.14.11.99 - RT I 1999, 82, 753) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.10.99 entered into force 14.11.99 - RT I 1999, 82, 753) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Toote ja teenuse ohutuse m&auml;&auml;ratlemise alused </eesti>
<inglise>Bases for determination of safety of products and services </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Toote ja teenuse ohutuse m&auml;&auml;ratlemise alused on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following are the bases for determining the safety of products and services: </inglise>
<eesti>1) toote &uuml;lesehitus, koostis, pakend ning tootja antud teave toote paigaldamiseks, kasutamiseks, hooldamiseks ja muuks otstarbeks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the structure, composition and packaging of the product and information provided by the producer for the assembly, use, maintenance and other purposes of the product; </inglise>
<eesti>2) m&otilde;ju teisele tootele, kui v&otilde;ib eeldada selle kasutamist koos teise tootega; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the effect on other products, where it is reasonably foreseeable that it will be used with other products; </inglise>
<eesti>3) toote esitlemine, m&auml;rgistus ja tootja antud teave turustamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the presentation and labelling of the product and information for marketing provided by the producer; </inglise>
<eesti>4) v&otilde;imalik oht tarbija sihtgruppidele, eriti lastele. </eesti>
<inglise>4) the potential risk to categories of consumers, in particular children. </inglise>
<eesti>(1 (1)) Vabariigi Valitsus v&otilde;i tema volitatud minister v&otilde;ib kehtestada erinevatele toodetele ohutusn&otilde;uded ja nendele n&otilde;uetele vastavuse t&otilde;endamise korra, arvestades toote n&otilde;uetele vastavuse t&otilde;endamise seaduses (RT I 1999, 92, 825) s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>(1 (1)) The Government of the Republic or a minister authorised thereby may establish safety requirements for different products and the procedure for attestation of the conformity with such requirements, taking into account the provisions of the Product Conformity Attestation Act (RT I 1999, 92, 825). </inglise>
<eesti>(08.11.2000 j&otilde;ust.02.12.2000 - RT I 2000, 86, 546) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.11.2000 entered into force 02.12.2000 - RT I 2000, 86, 546) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) (Kehtetu - 20.10.99 j&otilde;ust.14.11.99 - RT I 1999, 82, 753) </eesti>
<inglise>(2) (Repealed - 20.10.99 entered into force 14.11.99 - RT I 1999, 82, 753) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui seadusega v&otilde;i seaduse alusel ei ole toote ega teenuse ohutusn&otilde;udeid kehtestatud, hinnatakse ohutust Eesti standardeid arvestades. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If safety requirements for products or services are not established by or on the basis of an Act, safety shall be assessed having regard to Estonian standards. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui standardid puuduvad, arvestatakse tervise ja ohutuse tagamise head tava vastavas valdkonnas v&otilde;i tehnika ja tehnoloogia taset, samuti ohutust, mida toote ja teenuse tarbijad v&otilde;ivad m&otilde;istusp&auml;raselt eeldada. </eesti>
<inglise>If no standards exist, effect is given to good practice in respect of health and safety in the sector concerned, the state of the art and technology and to the safety which consumers of products and services may reasonably expect. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Tootja, teenuse osutaja ja levitaja kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Duties of Producers, Service Providers and Distributors </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Tootja kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Duties of producers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tootja k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, a producer is: </inglise>
<eesti>1) toote v&otilde;i selle osa valmistaja; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the manufacturer of the product or of a part thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>2) isik, kes esitleb ennast toote valmistajana ning lisab tootele oma nime, &auml;rinime, kaubam&auml;rgi v&otilde;i muu eraldusm&auml;rgi; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the person who presents himself as the manufacturer of the product and affixes his or her name, business name, trade mark or other distinctive mark to the product; </inglise>
<eesti>3) isik, kes toodet uuendab v&otilde;i seda t&auml;iendab v&otilde;i viimistleb; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the person who improves, reconditions or finishes the product; </inglise>
<eesti>4) tootja esindaja toote turustamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the manufacturer's representative in marketing the product; </inglise>
<eesti>5) toote importija, kui toote valmistajal ei ole Eestis esindajat; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the importer of the product if the manufacturer of the product has no representative in Estonia; </inglise>
<eesti>6) teised toote pakkujad turustusahelas niiv&otilde;rd, kuiv&otilde;rd nende tegevus m&otilde;jutab toote ohutusomadusi. </eesti>
<inglise>6) other suppliers of products in the supply chain in so far as their activities affect the safety properties of a product. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tootja on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A producer is required to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) saatma turule ja turustama ainult ohutut toodet; </eesti>
<inglise>1) place and distribute only safe products on the market; </inglise>
<eesti>2) m&auml;rkima tootele tootja identifitseerimist v&otilde;imaldava kirje; </eesti>
<inglise>2) label products with information which enables identification of the producer; </inglise>
<eesti>3) varustama toote kasutamisjuhendi, m&auml;rgistuse ja teabega, mis v&otilde;imaldab hinnata ja v&auml;ltida ohte toote sihip&auml;rase kasutamise ajal; </eesti>
<inglise>3) provide instructions for use, labelling and information with products which enable the assessment and avoidance of risks in the intended use of the products; </inglise>
<eesti>4) koguma teavet ja l&auml;bi vaatama tarbijate kaebusi turustatava toote kohta ning vajaduse korral tegema tootekatsetusi ja v&otilde;tma kasutusele abin&otilde;ud, et muuta ohtlikuks osutunud toode n&otilde;uetekohaseks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) collect information and investigate consumers' complaints regarding marketed products and, if necessary, conduct product testing and take measures to make changes to products which prove to be dangerous such that they comply with the requirements; </inglise>
<eesti>5) teavitama toote levitajaid ilmnenud ohtudest. </eesti>
<inglise>5) notify the distributors of products of risks which become evident. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenuse osutaja kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Duties of service providers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenuse osutaja on kohustatud pakkuma ja osutama ainult ohutut teenust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Service providers are required to offer and provide only safe services. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teenust pakkudes peab teenuse osutaja tagama tootele kehtestatud ohutusn&otilde;uete t&auml;itmise. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In providing services, a service provider shall ensure compliance with the safety requirements established for products. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Levitaja kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Duties of distributors </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Levitaja k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on toote turustaja v&otilde;i toote edasitoimetaja, kelle tegevus ei m&otilde;juta toote ohutusomadusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, a distributor is the marketer or supplier of a product whose activities do not affect the safety properties of the product. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Levitaja on kohustatud l&otilde;petama toote turustamise, mille kohta ta teab v&otilde;i oma valduses oleva teabe alusel saab oletada, et toode ei vasta ohutusn&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A distributor is required to terminate the marketing of a product if the distributor knows or can presume on the basis of information in the distributor's possession that the product does not comply with safety requirements. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Toote ja teenuse ohtudest informeerimise ja turult k&otilde;rvaldamise kohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Duty to inform of risks of products and services and to withdraw them from market </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tootja, teenuse osutaja ja levitaja peavad informeerima teisi tootjaid, teenuse osutajaid ja levitajaid ning turuj&auml;relevalveasutusi turustatavatel toodetel ja osutatavatel teenustel ilmnenud ohtudest ning tegema koost&ouml;&ouml;d nende ohtude &auml;rahoidmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Producers, service providers and distributors shall inform other producers, service providers, distributors and market supervisory authorities of risks which become evident in marketed products and services provided and shall co-operate to avoid such risks. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui ilmneb, et toode v&otilde;i teenus ei ole ohutu, peavad tootja, teenuse osutaja ja levitaja peatama selle turustamise v&otilde;i levitamise ja kaasa aitama sellise toote v&otilde;i teenuse turult k&otilde;rvaldamisele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If it becomes evident that a product or service is not safe, the producer, service provider and distributor shall suspend the marketing and distribution thereof and assist in the withdrawal of such product or service from the market. </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Turuj&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>Market Supervision </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Turuj&auml;relevalveasutused </eesti>
<inglise>Market supervisory authorities </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Turuj&auml;relevalveasutused on Tarbijakaitseamet ning teised ametid ja inspektsioonid seadustes ja turuj&auml;relevalveasutuste p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;rustes s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The market supervisory authorities are the Consumer Protection Board and other boards and inspectorates as provided by law and the statutes of the market supervisory authorities. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Turuj&auml;relevalveasutused korraldavad toote ja teenuse ohutuse j&auml;relevalvet turul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Market supervisory authorities organise supervision over the safety of products and services in the market. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Turuj&auml;relevalveasutused on kohustatud regulaarselt vahetama omavahel informatsiooni ja tegema koost&ouml;&ouml;d. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Market supervisory authorities are required to regularly exchange information and co-operate with one another. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Turuj&auml;relevalve korraldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Organisation of market supervision </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvi 8 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud asutuste j&auml;relevalveametnikud kontrollivad toote ja teenuse ohutust: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Supervisory officials of the authorities specified in subsection 8 (1) of this Act shall check the safety of products and services: </inglise>
<eesti>1) perioodiliselt; </eesti>
<inglise>1) periodically; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kui on kahtlus, et toode v&otilde;i teenus ei ole ohutu. </eesti>
<inglise>2) if there is doubt whether a product or service is safe. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametit&otilde;endi esitamise korral on j&auml;relevalveametnikul &otilde;igus oma &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon presentation of identification, supervisory officials have the right, for the performance of their duties, to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) takistamatult siseneda turule saatmiseks ettevalmistatud ning turustatavate toodete ladudesse; </eesti>
<inglise>1) unhindered access to warehouses of products prepared for delivery to the market and which are to be marketed; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kontrollida toodete n&otilde;uetekohasust t&otilde;endavaid dokumente; </eesti>
<inglise>2) review documents which attest the conformity of products to requirements; </inglise>
<eesti>3) n&otilde;uda tootjalt ja teenuse osutajalt teavet toote ja teenuse kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>3) require information about products and services from producers and service providers; </inglise>
<eesti>4) teha oma p&auml;devuse piires ettekirjutusi, m&auml;&auml;rata nende t&auml;itmise t&auml;htaegu ja kontrollida nende t&auml;itmist; </eesti>
<inglise>4) issue precepts within the limits of their competence, impose time limits for their implementation and monitor their implementation; </inglise>
<eesti>5) v&otilde;tta kontrollimiseks tasuta tooten&auml;idiseid, arvestades k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 7 s&auml;testatud toote kontrollimise kulude tasumise korda. </eesti>
<inglise>5) take samples of products for safety checks without charge, taking into account the procedure for payment of expenses for product checks provided for in subsection (7) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.10.99 j&otilde;ust.14.11.99 - RT I 1999, 82, 753) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.10.99 entered into force 14.11.99 - RT I 1999, 82, 753) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tooten&auml;idise ja teenuse kontrollimiseks tellib turuj&auml;relevalveasutus p&auml;devalt ettev&otilde;ttelt, asutuselt v&otilde;i organisatsioonilt hindamisteenuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Market supervisory authorities shall order assessment services from competent enterprises, agencies or organisations to check samples of products and services. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Hindamisteenus vormistatakse ekspertarvamusena, kus kirjeldatakse anal&uuml;&uuml;si ning katsetamis- ja ekspertiisitulemusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Assessment services shall be formalised as expert opinions which describe the analysis, and the results of testing and expert analysis. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Turuj&auml;relevalveasutusel on &otilde;igus toote ja teenuse kontrollimise tulemustest l&auml;htuvalt teha j&auml;rgmisi otsuseid: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Market supervisory authorities have the right to make the following decisions based on the results of checks of products and services: </inglise>
<eesti>1) keelata toote turustamine ja teenuse osutamine t&auml;htajaks, mis on vajalik nende ohutuse l&otilde;plikuks kontrollimiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to prohibit the marketing of a product or the provision of a service for a time limit necessary to conduct a final check on the safety thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>2) n&otilde;uda, et toodet turustades ja teenust osutades antakse lisateavet toote tarbimisel ja teenuse osutamisel ilmneda v&otilde;ivast ohust; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to require that, upon marketing a product or providing a service, additional information be provided concerning the risks which may become evident upon the use of the product or provision of the service; </inglise>
<eesti>3) n&otilde;uda tootjalt ja teenuse osutajalt, et ta m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htajaks teavitab tarbijat turustatud toote ja osutatud teenuse ilmnenud ohtudest ja toote v&otilde;i teenuse ohtlikkuse k&otilde;rvaldamise v&otilde;imalustest; </eesti>
<inglise>3) to require that, by a specified time limit, a producer and service provider inform consumers of risks which have become evident and the possibilities of eliminating the risks of a product or service; </inglise>
<eesti>4) n&otilde;uda ohtlikuks osutunud toote ja teenuse eemaldamist turult ja keelustada nende reklaam ning vajadusel n&otilde;uda toote h&auml;vitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>4) to require the withdrawal of a dangerous product or service from the market, prohibit the advertising thereof and, if necessary, require the destruction of such product. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui turuj&auml;relevalveasutus on tuvastanud toote v&otilde;i teenuse ohtlikkuse, kehtivad k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 5 punktides 2-4 esitatud &otilde;igused sellest olenemata, et toode v&otilde;i teenus on k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvi 2 l&otilde;ike 2 j&auml;rgi ohutu. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If a market supervisory authority establishes the risks of a product or service, the rights specified in clauses (5) 2) -4) of this section are valid regardless of whether the product or service is safe pursuant to subsection 2 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Toote v&otilde;i teenuse kontrollimiseks tellitud hindamisteenuse kulud tasub turuj&auml;relevalveasutus ja tagastab tooten&auml;idise v&otilde;i h&uuml;vitab selle maksumuse, kui ekspertarvamuse kohaselt toode on ohutu. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The market supervisory authorities shall bear the expenses of assessment services which are ordered for product or service checks and shall return the product samples or compensate for the value thereof if, on the basis of an expert opinion, the product is safe. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui ekspertarvamuse kohaselt ei ole toode v&otilde;i teenus ohutu, tasub kulutused vastavalt tootja v&otilde;i teenuse osutaja. </eesti>
<inglise>If, on the basis of an expert opinion, a product or service is not safe, the expenses shall be borne by the producer or service provider. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui tootjat v&otilde;i teenuse osutajat ei ole v&otilde;imalik kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata, tasub kulutused levitaja. </eesti>
<inglise>If the producer or service provider cannot be determined, the expenses shall be borne by the distributor. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.10.99 j&otilde;ust.14.11.99 - RT I 1999, 82, 753) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.10.99 entered into force 14.11.99 - RT I 1999, 82, 753) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;relevalveametniku ettekirjutuse ja turuj&auml;relevalveasutuse otsuse tegemise v&otilde;i muu toimingu vaidlustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Appeal of precept issued by supervisory official, or decision or other act of market supervisory authority </inglise>
<eesti>Kui tootja, teenuse osutaja v&otilde;i levitaja ei n&otilde;ustu j&auml;relevalveametniku ettekirjutuse v&otilde;i turuj&auml;relevalveasutuse otsusega v&otilde;i muu toimingu tulemusega, v&otilde;ib ta esitada kaebuse halduskohtusse k&uuml;mne p&auml;eva jooksul ettekirjutuse v&otilde;i otsuse tegemisest v&otilde;i muu toimingu tulemusest teada saamisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>A producer, service provider or distributor who disagrees with a precept issued by a supervisory official, or a decision or the result of another act of a market supervisory authority may file an appeal with an administrative court within ten days after becoming aware of the issue of the precept, making of the decision or the result of another act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalikkuse teavitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Informing the public </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Turuj&auml;relevalveasutus on kohustatud avalikkust teavitama konkreetse toote ja teenuse ohtlikkusest &uuml;hes &uuml;leriigilise levikuga p&auml;evalehes, vajaduse korral teiste meediakanalite kaudu ning muul v&otilde;imalikul viisil. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Market supervisory authorities are required to inform the public of the risks of a specific product or service in a daily national newspaper and, if necessary, through other media and in other possible ways. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui turuj&auml;relevalve k&auml;igus on kindlaks tehtud, et toode v&otilde;i teenus ei ole ohutu ja seda toodet turustatakse v&otilde;i teenust osutatakse v&auml;lisriigis, siis teavitab Tarbijakaitseamet seda v&auml;lisriiki tuvastatud ohtudest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If in the course of market supervision it is determined that a product or service is not safe and the product is marketed or the service is provided in a foreign state, the Consumer Protection Board shall inform the foreign state of the established risks. </inglise>
<eesti>Vabariigi Valitsuse m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatakse nimetatud teavitamise tingimused ja kord. </eesti>
<inglise>The conditions and procedure for provision of such information are established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Liability </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>F&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Liability of natural persons </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide rikkumise eest kannab f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik distsiplinaar-, tsiviil-, haldus- v&otilde;i kriminaalvastutust seadusega etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Natural persons bear disciplinary, civil, administrative or criminal liability for violations of this Act and legislation established on the basis thereof pursuant to the procedure prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku haldusvastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Administrative liability of legal persons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) J&auml;relevalveametniku ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise eest m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv kuni 50 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A fine of up to 50 000 kroons is imposed for failure to comply with a precept issued by a supervisory official. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Turuj&auml;relevalveasutuse otsuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise eest m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv kuni 150 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A fine of up to 150 000 kroons is imposed for failure to comply with a decision issued by a market supervisory authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Juriidilise isiku poolt k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 nimetatud &otilde;iguserikkumise asja arutamise ja temale karistuse m&auml;&auml;ramise &otilde;igus on halduskohtunikul. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Administrative court judges have the right to hear and impose punishments for matters concerning offences specified in subsections (1) and (2) of this section by legal persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Menetlus k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 s&auml;testatud juriidilise isiku haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise asjas, kaasa arvatud karistuse m&auml;&auml;ramine ja vaidlustamine ning j&otilde;ustunud halduskaristuse otsuse t&auml;itmine toimub haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustikus (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 1999, 41, 496; 58, 608; 95, 843; 2000, 10, 58; 25, 141; 28, 167; 29, 169; 40, 247; 49, 301; 49, 305; 51, 321; 54, 346; 348; 351; 55, 361; 58, 376; 84, 533; 86, 544) ja t&auml;itemenetluse seadustikus (RT I 1993, 49, 693; 1997, 43/44, 723; 1998, 41/42, 625; 51, 756; 61, 981; 1999, 18, 302; 27, 380; 95, 845; 103, 1695; 2000, 28, 167; 35, 222; 58, 376) kehtestatud korras, kui k&auml;esolev seadus ei s&auml;testa teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Proceedings in matters concerning administrative offences set out in subsections (1) and (2) of this section by legal persons, including the imposition of punishments, appeal of punishments and execution of administrative punishment orders in force are carried out pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Code of Administrative Offences (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 1999, 41, 496; 58, 608; 95, 843; 2000, 10, 58; 25, 141; 28, 167; 29, 169; 40, 247; 49, 301; 49, 305; 51, 321; 54, 346; 348; 351; 55, 361; 58, 376; 84, 533; 86, 544) and the Code of Enforcement Procedure (RT I 1993, 49, 693; 1997, 43/44, 723; 1998, 41/42, 625; 51, 756; 61, 981; 1999, 18, 302; 27, 380; 95, 845; 103, 1695; 2000, 28, 167; 35, 222; 58, 376), unless otherwise provided by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>Haldusprotokolli koostamine </eesti>
<inglise>Preparation of administrative offence reports </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvi 13 l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 s&auml;testatud juriidilise isiku haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste kohta protokolli koostamise &otilde;igus on j&auml;relevalveametnikul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Supervisory officials have the right to prepare reports regarding the administrative offences provided for in subsections 13 (1) and (2) of this Act by legal persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Protokolli m&auml;rgitakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An administrative offence report sets out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) selle koostamise aeg ja koht; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the time and place of preparation of the report; </inglise>
<eesti>2) asutuse nimi ja aadress, kelle nimel protokoll koostatakse; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the name and address of the agency in whose name the report is prepared; </inglise>
<eesti>3) protokolli koostanud isiku ees- ja perekonnanimi ning ametikoht; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the given name, surname and official title of the person who prepares the report; </inglise>
<eesti>4) haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja nimetus ja asukoht; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the name and seat of the administrative offender; </inglise>
<eesti>5) haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja esindaja ees- ja perekonnanimi ning ametikoht; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the given name, surname and official title of the representative of the administrative offender; </inglise>
<eesti>6) haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise koht, aeg ja kirjeldus; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the place, time and description of the administrative offence; </inglise>
<eesti>7) viide k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvi 13 vastavale l&otilde;ikele, mis n&auml;eb ette vastutuse selle haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise eest; </eesti>
<inglise>7) a reference to the subsection of &sect; 13 of this Act which prescribes liability for the administrative offence; </inglise>
<eesti>8) haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja esindaja seletus; </eesti>
<inglise>8) an explanation from the representative of the administrative offender; </inglise>
<eesti>9) muud asja lahendamiseks vajalikud andmed. </eesti>
<inglise>9) other information necessary for determination of the matter. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja keeldub protokollile alla kirjutamast, tehakse selle kohta vastav kanne. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the administrative offender refuses to sign the report, an entry shall be made in the report regarding such refusal. </inglise>
